name: beta-galactosidase
classes: Glycosidases, i.e. enzymes that hydrolyse O- and S-glycosyl compounds
reaction: Hydrolysis of terminal non-reducing beta-D-galactose residues in beta-D-galactosides
comment: Some enzymes in this group hydrolyse alpha-L-arabinosides; some animal enzymes also hydrolyse beta-D-fucosides and beta-D-glucosides; cf. EC 3.2.1.108 lactase.
